# Metric-aware Einstein summation (spec §04): the `metric: …` statement form
# lowers to a `metricsum(metric, [.axes…], expr)` call. `.name^` and `.name_`
# are the upper / lower variance markers. Composition of three Lorentz
# transformations as (1,1)-tensors under metric `g` (the spec's example).
g = eye(4)
L1 = eye(4)
L2 = eye(4)
L3 = eye(4)
g: L[.mu^, .rho_] := L1[.mu^, .nu_] * L2[.nu^, .sigma_] * L3[.sigma^, .rho_]
